C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                            FY 2025     FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: Space Development Agency R&E                                                                                                              379.182     453.023      313.738
Description: Research and development activities to support development, demonstration, and fielding of a resilient military
sensing and data transport capability via a proliferated space architecture in Low Earth Orbit (LEO). The funds support the
development of an increasingly broad set of technologies (including alternative navigation solutions, advanced missile tracking,
intelligence signal fusion algorithms, integrated battle management algorithms, advanced optical communications, and next
generation tactical data links) that are critical to delivering a robust initial warfighting capability in the Proliferated Warfighter Space
Architecture (PWSA).

FY 2026 Plans:
Tranche 0
- Continue to conduct post-Capstone demonstrations and experimentations with warfighters.
- Begin end-of-life operations on select satellites.

Tranche 1
- Resolve anomalous behavior in system interoperability and compatibility, including optical communications, space-to-ground
radio frequency (RF), Link 16, and Networking.
- Continue mission engineering support activities including Concept of Operations (CONOPS) and Concept of Employment
(CONEMP) development, user segment integration, developmental and operational test planning, and characterization and
modeling of system performance targeting advanced use case capabilities.
- Augment User Guides and Interface Control Documents (ICDs) and conduct integration and test activities to onboard additional
Transport mission partners.

Tranche 2
- Support risk reduction of Transport Layer Tranche 2 (TLT2) satellites, ground systems, and integration.




