FY 2025 Accomplishments: Conducted acquisition and began progress of effort to provide the following
capabilities: Rapidly prototype, evaluate, and iterate on a product that provides human operators with an
enhanced human-machine interface (HMI) designed and integrated to facilitate real-time monitoring and alert
operators to emerging threats to low Earth orbit satellite systems. Refine ML models and integrate capabilities
into operational systems providing actionable information for comprehensive triage and response management
by space operators. Execute field tests at various ranges that can create the expected threat environments.
FY 2026 Plans: Rapidly prototype, evaluate, and iterate on a product that provides human operators with an
enhanced human-machine interface (HMI) designed and integrated to facilitate real-time monitoring and alert
operators to emerging threats to low Earth orbit satellite systems. The initial focus was on the development and
testing of threat induced anomaly detection in bus and mission payload systems by using machine learning
(ML) models created to monitor satellite telemetry data. This continuing effort refines these ML models and
integrates these capabilities into operational systems providing actionable information for comprehensive triage
and response management by space operators.
