E. Acquisition Strategy
Partners for these activities include DoW research centers, small businesses, non-traditional defense contractors, large defense contractors, commercial space
providers, Federally Funded Research and Development Centers, University Affiliated Research Centers, Missile Defense Agency (MDA), Space Systems Command
(SSC), Space Operations Command (SpOC), Space Training and Readiness Command (STARCOM), and Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA).
SDA is also a potential transition partner for technology developers seeking to conduct on-orbit experimentation and prototyping. SDA's Tranche 1 Transport Layer
and Tranche 2 Transport Layer space systems are being acquired via Firm Fixed Price contracts conducted in accordance with Other Transaction Authority (OT) for
prototyping processes.




