C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025     FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: Space Weather Analysis and Forecast System (SWAFS) Radio Frequency Ionospheric Scintillation Application (RISA                      0.836       0.843        3.581
version 2) software upgrade
Description: Funding will be provided to Peraton to manage SWAFS prototyping efforts to include SWAFS RISA version 2, a
model identified in an Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) Analysis of Alternatives (AoA) to upgrade software allowing use
of model algorithms that utilize sensor packages on the Constellation Observing System to monitor Meteorology, Ionosphere,
and Climate (COSMIC II) to understand space environment conditions affecting satellites and communications. Johns Hopkins
University/Applied Physics Lab (JHU/APL) will perform model upgrades to Ionospheric Data Assimilation - Four Dimensional
(IDA4D) to ensure compatibility with a Gov Cloud environment within the SWAFS Space Domain Awareness Environmental
Toolkit - for Defense (SET4D) baseline.

FY 2026 Plans:
Peraton to continue development of upgrade to the Space Weather High Frequency Communication Propagation Model, in
conjunction with the AFRL (Air Force Research Lab) development of the Scintillation Nowcast Forecast Model Update, that
identifies space environment impacts to DoW and Intelligence Community communications to and through space, and additional
Electromagnetic spectrum interference hazard assessment tools (EMI-HAS).

