Title: Information Assurance, Security/Compatibility Certification, and Test/Evaluation                                                 16.002      13.350          0.000
Description: Develop, implement, and maintain Global Positioning System (GPS) security programs. Develop policy, strategy
and resource requirements for GPS User Equipment, security certification and compatibility certification. Security certification,
compatibility certification, and security approval ensures future military GPS receivers protect Critical Program Information (CPI)
and continue working in all environments and concepts of operations called for by U.S. Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM).

FY 2026 Plans:
Conduct initial and delta security certification activities for all GPS receivers. Conduct security evaluations/tests for Selective
Availability Anti-Spoofing Module (SAASM) and other legacy GPS receiver equipment. Review, approve, and authorize SAASM,
M-Code receivers, and certified legacy receiver certified platforms and integrated applications for all of DoW. Provide technical
support to develop, validate and process engineering changes. Provide Mobile Crypto Initialization Capability (MCIC) for SAASM
receivers and develop Modernized CIC for M-code receivers. Provide Military Standard Order (MSO) certification for GPS Precise
Positioning Service (PPS) receivers for integration into aviation platforms. Conduct MGUE Inc 2 hand-held ASIC early Integration
& Testing (I&T). Continue to provide Military Standard Order support to portfolio of airborne GPS receiving programs. Update the
Protection Profile (PP) to Process Requirement Documents (PRD) to guarantee the integrity of GPS Critical Program Information
(CPI) for the benefit of the warfighter.
FY 2027 Plans:
MGUE Inc 2 program transfers from United States Space Force (USSF) to United States Air Force (USAF) in FY 2027.
