Note
This program, BA 7, PE 1203154SF, project 676602, Space Based Interceptor, is a new start.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This program continues funding for Space Data Network (SDN) in support of United States Space Force (USSF) Space Based Interceptors (SBI), the effort to develop a
space-based weapon system to counter-Intercontinental Ballistic Missiles (ICBM) and Counter-hypersonic glide vehicles (HGV).

 The Long-Range Kill Chains PE contains activities for the Space Data Network-Space Link (SDN-SL) program. This program leverages the United States Space Force
 (USSF) multi-vendor Space Data Network - Backbone (SDN-B) program to enhance an integrated constellation to provide the communication layer for the Space Based
 Interceptors (SBI). This project is incorrectly labeled "Space Based Interceptor".

 PE1203154SF previously contained efforts that contributed to the creation of the Space Data Network and associated auxiliary payloads. Some of these efforts have had
 their funding aligned to the new Space Data Network PE1203636SF, and the remaining related efforts will eventually follow in future budget submissions.

 PE1203154SF also previously contained activities to support delivery of Golden Dome for America (GDA).

 This program is in Budget Activity 7, Operational System Development because this budget activity includes development efforts to upgrade systems that have been
 fielded or have received approval for full rate production and anticipate production funding in the current or subsequent fiscal year.




