algorithms for DoW Weather Center models and assess on-orbit data for operational suitability.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase reflects the transfer of the Muon SBEM variant demonstration effort previously executed from the EWS
FY26 Major Thrust of this program element. Includes maturing and integrating commercial EM capabilities, including on-orbit
demonstrations and integration with DoW Weather Center models.
Title: Commercial GEO EO/IR                                                                                                                 -        0.000         37.940
Description: The Commercial GEO EO/IR capabilities provides overhead persistent Theatre Weather Imagery (TWI) for near-real
time weather data in the INDOPACOM and CENTCOM AOR in addition to providing low latency data for Cloud Characterization
(CC) weather models. The Geostationary (GEO) EO/IR capabilities is a follow-on to the EWS-G satellite system with projected
end of life in 2030. The Commercial GEO EO/IR capabilities includes rapid development and deployment of commercial
Geostationary (GEO) Electro-optical/infrared EO/IR solutions, to include but not limited to, commercially hosting compact GEO
EO/IR sensors. The Commercial GEO EO/IR capabilities effort includes upgrades to the existing EWS-G ground infrastructure to
enable processing of current generation GEO EO/IR high data rate imagery from Civil and Commercial GEO EO/IR satellites.

The Commercial GEO EO/IR capabilities includes contractor operated Command and Control, mission data processing and
mission data distribution. The requirement for persistent GEO EO/IR coverage is necessary to meet a Global 1-hour refresh
requirement as documented in Joint Requirements Oversight Council Memo (JROCM) 101-24.

FY 2026 Plans:
N/A
