Remarks

E. Acquisition Strategy
In accordance with the approved space-based Environmental Monitoring (SBEM) Acquisition Strategy (Sep 2020), the EWS program will continue to use Other
Transaction Authority (OTA) to competitively pursue technological advancements in smaller sensor designs and leveraging commercial-based capabilities to develop
the most optimal solution to long-term Cloud Characterization and Theater Weather Imagery needs. The Phase II modernized pathfinder efforts will include OTA under
Firm Fixed Price (FFP) contracts for technology risk reduction and operational demonstration efforts, while minimizing developmental cost risks. FFP efforts under Phase
II have resulted in considerable cost savings for the government after conversion from Cost Plus, which enable the funding of the Ops Demo #2 launch vehicle within
current budget profiles. The Environmental Monitoring Data As A Service (DaaS) Acquisition Strategy will guide EM DaaS commercial and GEO EO/IR capabilities
acquisitions. The EM DaaS Acquisition Strategy is built around the Environmental Monitoring (EM) Mission Area Acquisition Framework (MAAF) which is a mission
engineering process for prioritizing validated requirements, identifying capability gaps based on the civil and international Family of Systems, and leverages non-
materiel solutions and commercial EM DaaS data buys before building dedicated Space Force-owned systems. The EM Data as a Service (DaaS) Acquisition Strategy
identifies a progressive approach to maturing nascent Commercial Weather technologies from a concept stage through on-orbit demonstrations and finally procurement
of operational weather data. The Space Force will partner with industry to fund technologies which meet prioritized validated requirements and collaborate in on-orbit
demonstrations for operational suitability assessments. The Space Force will only procure commercial weather data that has passed an assessment performed with
Department of War (DoW) weather centers and civil partners to ensure the data is ready for operational forecasts. Additionally, the EM DaaS Acquisition Strategy
addresses commercial acquisition approaches for the Geostationary (GEO) Electro-optical/infrared (EO/IR) capabilities to include innovative commercial hosting of a
compact GEO EO/IR imager design.




