674671 (Enterprise Training Services Development - ETSD). Prior year funding and justification narratives remain under those
program (PE) justification materials.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges to improve: infrastructure; hardware; software; integrated
data transport; Command, Control and Communications; sensors, surrogates, and other existing capabilities
- Continue evolving fielded Electromagnetic Warfare (EW) digital training modeling & simulation (M&S) capabilities environment
- Continue developing and maturing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) capabilities for
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Continue development of advanced combat training capabilities, including tools and applications for training, exercises and
wargames
- Continue enhancing digital range capabilities via Commercial Solutions Openings (CSOs) and deliver capabilities to enhance,
extend, and scale existing fielded distributed training capabilities and associated tools
- Continue coordination and provisioning of near-term training and tactics solutions
- Continue buildout of Integration Accelerator collaboration capability
- Continue maintenance, sustainment, and tech refresh of current test capabilities
- Continue distributed training capability development via Indefinite Delivery/Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) vendor pool to extend
distributed training capabilities to additional operational units at their home stations
- Continue to modify and integrate mission simulator software into the synthetic space environment to expand multi-mission
training and exercise capability
- Continue software development and releases of Artificial Intelligence to augment aggressors in support of training and exercises
- Develop and/or modify red threat models and related training systems per operational priorities and evolving/emerging threats
- Continue development of distributed enterprise cloud and data management solution
