Note
In FY2027 this program (PE 1206617SF), project 644441 (Operational Test & Training Infrastructure) was created to consolidate funding and justification narratives for
PE1206759SF (Major T&E Investment-Space), project 644598 (National Space Test and Training Complex-NSTTC), and PE1203174SF (Space Innovation, Integration
and Rapid Technology Development-SIIRTD), project 674671 (Enterprise Training Services Development-ETSD) to optimize management of OTTI activities as well as
improve clarity and traceability for reporting these activities.

 The efforts contained herein are not a new start.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
SYD 81 is developing, operating and sustaining Operational Test & Training Infrastructure (OTTI) (Project 64441) for Guardians to improve test and training across the
following mission areas: Combat Power, Missile Warning & Tracking, Space Domain Awareness, Launch, Position Navigation and Timing, Satellite Communications,
Weather, Science & Technology and Test & Evaluation. As a result, the Service will improve readiness and operational reach of existing force structure through the
resilient Infrastructure, equipment, and personnel training.

 This program continues funding United States Space Force (USSF) OTTI as the service-level effort to test, train, and build combat credibility for National Security Space
 weapon systems and joint force space capabilities. OTTI is primarily a portfolio of systems being developed with intended delivery to the National Space Test and
 Training Complex (NSTTC) under the command of Space Training & Readiness Command (STARCOM).

 OTTI has 4 lines of effort (LOEs): the Physical/Live Test and Training Range LOE, the Digital Test & Training Range LOE, a Test & Training Infrastructure LOE that
 supports the first two LOEs, and a Space Force Operational Readiness LOE focused on operation and sustainment of delivered systems. These efforts encompass the
 acquisition, development, integration, and sustainment activities to test and evaluate the performance of Department of War (DoW) space systems; train space operators
 for combat operations in, from, and through space; and develop and validate the tactics, techniques and procedures to support combat operations.

 This program falls within the Science & Technology (S&T) and Test & Evaluation (T&E) mission area which provides for the validation of combat credibility for Combat
 Power space systems and the validation of Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs) for space superiority. In addition, the program develops advanced training
 systems and networks to improve the readiness of all mission area combat units. Space Force investment program interdependencies include:
 RDT&E Budget Line Items: Defense Research Sciences (0601102SF); Major T&E Investments - Space (1206759SF); Small Business Innovation Research
 (1205502SF); Space Advanced Tech Dev / Demo (1206616SF); Space Innov Intg & Rapid Tech Dev (1203174SF); Space Rapid Capabilities Office (1206857SF);

