Title: Space Development and Production                                                                                                            -        0.000     1,266.878
Description: Space Development and Production builds upon the 4+ Years of Space Segment Prototyping and delivers the
next generation of NC3 Strategic SATCOM to the warfighter. The ESS Space Development and Production contract will design,
develop, build, test, and deliver resilient, cybersecure space vehicles that ensure communications through all warfighting
environments. This effort will initiate the non-recurring engineering for the development and production of Space Vehicles 1- 4 in
order to achieve IOC by 2032 and continuing through FOC.

FY 2026 Plans:
(Project 643725 BA 04) Continue significant Non-Recurring Engineering (NRE) activities covering essential engineering, process
documents, and building engineering models of flight hardware to lead up to a unit and system level critical design reviews
(CDRs) in FY 2027. Additional NRE activities include developing and integrating auxiliary payloads, designing the ESS Payload
Emulator and supporting SoSI activities with the ESS ground and crypto vendors. ESS is an extremely complex system of
systems. The ESS space, ground, and crypto vendors will need to collaborate further to update and refine interface control
documents, communication protocols, and software imaging formats.

The program will procure additional critical hardware items necessary for the build and test of space vehicles (SVs) 1 and 2.
The ESS SV vendor will continue developmental test activities with a crypto engineering development model (EDM) to reduce
integration risk with the payload ECU. This activity will enable the successful integration of ESS crypto production representative
articles (PRAs) in FY 2026. The ESS program will also continue software development for the payload and bus flight software and
continue building digital twins to support the ESS digital engineering ecosystem. The digital engineering ecosystem is critical for
design and integration risk reduction activities prior to building ESS space vehicles.

Ancillary activities will involve starting or continuing special studies for survivability, resiliency, risk reduction, and architectural
trades.



