Competition during space prototyping energized the industrial base in strategic SATCOM; injected diverse technical processes and integration approaches; burned down
risks as early as possible; and decreased traditional fielding timelines to support a more resilient, responsive architecture against emerging threats. Success during
competitive rapid-prototyping informed the follow-on Space Development and Production competition. In June 2025, the SAE approved the Space Segment to transition
to Milestone B and ESS awarded the Space Development and Production contract for SV 1-4 on 3 July 2025. The program office will return to the SAE after Space CDR
to award the Space Production Follow-on contract for SV 5-7.




