C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Description: TacRS will leverage rapid, agile, and end-to-end acquisition processes to quickly evolve the design of future TacRS
missions. This approach will enable timely integration and readiness for launch call-up, Combatant Commander (CCMD) tasking,
and procurement of capabilities based on current threats and priorities.

FY 2026 Plans:
Support the development, readiness, launch, and operations for the VICTUS HAZE, VICTUS SOL and other VICTUS missions.
The two maneuverable, prepositioned Space Domain Awareness (SDA) missions, VICTUS SURGO and VICTUS SALO, will
begin integration and testing in the second half of FY 2026. Support range efforts and ground infrastructure developments
that will provide necessary equipment, software, procedures and personnel to enable and support future TacRS missions.
Continue acquisition of future operational missions that require both rapid launch capabilities and maneuverable, prepositioned
capabilities. Support concept and capability development that enables the rapid use of commercial capabilities. Continue to evolve
new tactically responsive space capabilities that include launch, satellites, control systems, and concept of operations using
emerging and extant commercial launch and satellite providers while leveraging U.S. Government partnerships, and international
opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to, program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2027 Plans:
In FY 2027, funding will be used to finalize assembly, integration and testing of the two maneuverable, prepositioned SDA
TacRS missions, VICTUS SURGO and VICTUS SALO. In addition, funding will be used to support follow-on SDA operational
missions requiring both rapid launch and maneuverable, prepositioned capabilities. FY 2027 funding will enhance navigation
payloads allowing for improved on-orbit positional information for space characterization of resident space objects, operationalize
prepositioned capabilities, and establish the rapid reaction force structure of having one space vehicle in production and one
completed space vehicle and launch vehicle on hand ready for mission call up to execute rapid launch.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase in FY 2026 to FY 2027 funding is due to establishing the rapid launch cadence of having a space vehicle completed
and ready for launch while another space vehicle is being built.
