Remarks$$, $$TacRS prioritizes commercial, fixed-priced contracts to take advantage of evolving commercial capabilities, technology advancements, and reduced production
timelines to rapidly deliver minimum viable warfighter solutions. This iterative nature of incremental, commercially-based system improvements that builds upon prior
missions will allow TacRS to achieve 18-24-month space vehicle build and launch timelines resulting in substantially reduced cost when compared to traditional satellite
procurements. TacRS has established contracts with multiple commercial satellite vendors providing an initial pool of contractors from which to procure satellites and
will continue to expand the list of available vendors to increase the Government's available options to provide maximum flexibility and competition. Working with multiple
small start-up businesses through fixed price contracts has allowed an increased understanding of industry partner capabilities and technical solutions available that
can deliver unique performance capabilities that meet the TacRS responsive timelines and operational deployment objectives. TacRS will also utilize existing (and if
necessary establish new) open competitive launch service, ground operations contracts, Small Business Innovative Research contracts, and Other Transaction Authority
(OTA) Agreements to provide an end-to-end TacRS capability.

