A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Space Safari Office is developing, prototyping, and executing the Tactically Responsive Space (TacRS) (project 643835) to deliver space control functions to
Guardians and Combatant Commands. As a result of these activities, the Service will deliver capabilities to augment, supplement, and integrate with Allies, partners,
and commercial space companies to Space Force units.

 TacRS rapidly integrates and deploys space-based end-to-end capabilities in response to Combatant Commander (CCMD) urgent needs for power projection and
 characterization. TacRS missions will be capable of entering operations and generating effects on tactically relevant timelines. The near-term focus of TacRS is to
 establish these foundational concepts enabling the Space Force to establish the necessary capabilities, processes, concept of operations, and tactics, techniques and
 procedures to enable a rapid response. In FY 2026, funding will be used to finalize an early operational Space Domain Awareness (SDA) capability that will involve a
 rapid call-up, launch, and space vehicle operations. In addition, funding will be used to develop the maneuverable, prepositioned SDA TacRS missions. Furthermore,
 funding will be used to support follow-on SDA operational missions requiring both rapid launch and maneuverable, prepositioned capabilities. Finally, funding will be
 used to mature new TacRS concepts including, but not limited to, the ability to quickly utilize commercial capabilities.

 This program falls within the Combat Power mission area which provides the systems required to protect and defend space-based capabilities and ensure space
 superiority by enabling and executing combat operations in space. Program interdependencies include: Counterspace Operations (1203936SF); Counterspace
 Systems (1206421SF); Defense Recon Support Activities (1203159SF); National Space Defense Center (1203620SF); National Space Defense Center - MIP
 (1203621SF); Space Control Technology (1206438SF); Space Intelligence Activities (1203375SF); Space Superiority ISR (1203330SF); Rocket Systems Launch
 Program (1206860SF); and Rapid Resilient Command & Control (1206772SF).

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Research, Development, Test & Evaluation, Space Force, Tactically Responsive Space (TacRS) includes $29,800 thousand of
 discretionary and $135,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $164,800 thousand.

 This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
 addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

 This effort is in Budget Activity 4, Advanced Component Development and Prototypes (ACD&P), because efforts are necessary to evaluate integrated technologies,
 representative modes or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.


